    "color_palette": "ALBAIK crimson-red (the dominant field) paired with golden-yellow as the co-hero accent. Red governs the background/wordmark mass; yellow governs the call-to-action discs, the secondary wordmark, and the packaging pattern. This red+yellow pair is the locked brand primary; navy and white are secondaries. · Warm, deep, and saturated — a center-lit radial glow (bright core behind the hero food, falling to dark maroon/charred edges), giving a dramatic studio-ember mood rather than a flat pastel. The spicy/'حراق' line darkens to near-black with orange ember sparks; occasion posts swap to a deep starry navy. Tone is consistently rich and high-contrast, never light/airy except the deliberate clean-white promo cuts.",
    "style_descriptor": "Glossy high-gloss commercial fast-food photography: single hard key light producing crisp specular highlights on melted cheese, glistening sauce drips and sesame-bun sheen, deep contact shadows, and a saturated color-field backdrop with radial vignette. Surfaces look freshly fried and juicy (visible oil sheen, steam-implied moisture). Hero food shot close and slightly above eye level on a clean or reflective surface; ember-spark particles added on the spicy line; tightly retouched, appetite-maximized, not documentary/natural.",
    "lighting": null,
    "people_in_frame": "none",
    "filter_style": null,
    "style_register": null,
    "identity_dna": "Two thick BROASTED golden-crispy chicken breast fillets stacked one above the other, each with a craggy deep-fried crumb crust, separated and crowned by melted cheese that drapes over the edges, bright-green sliced dill pickles peeking between the layers, and Albaik's twin sauces — the white garlic ثومية and the pinkish-orange cocktail (مسحب) sauce — oozing down the sides. The bun is Albaik's own pale, soft, SEEDLESS round bun (a plain glossy top crown, NOT a sesame burger bun), generously domed, against the brand's red backdrop.",
    "color_field_palette": "Two brand-owned color fields only: (1) ALBAIK signature deep brick-crimson red (≈ a rich tomato-to-maroon red, NOT a generic KFC bright red — it reads slightly cooler and deeper), almost always rendered as a center-bright radial glow falling to dark maroon at the edges; (2) ALBAIK golden-yellow (the price-disc / wordmark / packaging-pattern yellow). A deep navy-blue field is the owned occasion variant (night/Eid/Ramadan/fish). White is the owned neutral (the packaging bag). A color-blocking chain may fill the frame ONLY from {crimson-red, golden-yellow, navy-blue, white} — never a borrowed reference red/orange.",
